<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1691,2027]" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,357,1796,1819]" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">Comparisons.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[365,645,1795,1819]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudochromidae" genus="Pseudochromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yamasakii">
<emphasis box="[365,645,1795,1819]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">Pseudochromis yamasakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents an ambiguous combination of characters at couplet 55 of Gill’s (2004) key to 
<taxonomicName box="[301,464,1830,1854]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudochromidae" genus="Pseudochromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[301,464,1830,1854]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">Pseudochromis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. It has 25 segmented dorsal-fin rays, characteristic of couplet 55a (which identifies 
<taxonomicName authority="Gill &amp; Randall 1998" authorityName="Gill &amp; Randall" authorityYear="1998" box="[151,448,1864,1888]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudochromidae" genus="Pseudochromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="litus">
<emphasis box="[151,222,1864,1888]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">P. litus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gill" box="[228,448,1865,1888]" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" refString="Gill, A. C. &amp; Randall, J. E. (1998) Five new species of the dottyback genus Pseudochromis from Indonesia (Teleostei: Pseudochromidae). Revue francaise d'Aquariologie Herpetologie, 25, 17 - 26." type="journal article" year="1998">Gill &amp; Randall 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), and sometimes has a dark spot in the pectoral fin axil, which is characteristic of couplet 55b (leading to 
<taxonomicName authority="Gill &amp; Randall 1998" authorityName="Gill &amp; Randall" authorityYear="1998" box="[272,636,1899,1923]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudochromidae" genus="Pseudochromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aurulentus">
<emphasis box="[272,412,1899,1923]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">P. aurulentus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gill" box="[419,636,1900,1923]" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" refString="Gill, A. C. &amp; Randall, J. E. (1998) Five new species of the dottyback genus Pseudochromis from Indonesia (Teleostei: Pseudochromidae). Revue francaise d'Aquariologie Herpetologie, 25, 17 - 26." type="journal article" year="1998">Gill &amp; Randall 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Randall &amp; McCosker 1989" authorityName="Randall &amp; McCosker" authorityYear="1989" box="[688,1064,1899,1923]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudochromidae" genus="Pseudochromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pylei">
<emphasis box="[688,766,1899,1923]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">P. pylei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Randall" box="[772,1064,1900,1923]" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" refString="Randall, J. E. &amp; McCosker, J. E. (1989) Pseudochromis pylei (Teleostei: Perciformes; Pseudochromidae) a new dottyback from Indonesia. Revue Francaise d'Aquariologie Herpetologie, 16, 7 - 10." type="journal article" year="1989">Randall &amp; McCosker 1989</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). It differs from all three species in having: fewer predorsal scales (15 versus 
<quantity box="[615,712,1935,1958]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.588" metricValueMax="5.842" metricValueMin="5.334" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" unit="in" value="22.0" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="21.0">21–23 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName box="[722,797,1934,1958]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudochromidae" genus="Pseudochromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="litus">
<emphasis box="[722,797,1934,1958]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">P. litus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<quantity box="[813,910,1935,1958]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.968999999999999" metricValueMax="6.604000000000001" metricValueMin="5.3340000000000005" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" unit="in" value="23.5" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="21.0">21–26 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName box="[919,1062,1934,1958]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudochromidae" genus="Pseudochromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aurulentus">
<emphasis box="[919,1062,1934,1958]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">P. aurulentus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<quantity box="[1126,1223,1935,1958]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.715" metricValueMax="6.35" metricValueMin="5.08" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" unit="in" value="22.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="20.0">20–25 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName box="[1233,1314,1934,1958]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudochromidae" genus="Pseudochromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pylei">
<emphasis box="[1233,1314,1934,1958]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">P. pylei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), with less extensive predorsal scalation (scales extending anteriorly only to anterior AIO pores versus to a point ranging from the posterior nasal pores to the posterior nostrils in the other three species).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159341/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="299" targetBox="[212,1383,175,1032]" targetPageId="3">
